## Reliability pyramid

The higher up the pyramid, the more permanent the rule. Critical mistakes go higher.

1. **Session memory** — this turn only. Forgotten on reset.
2. **`core/episodes.jsonl`** — corrections from operator, scored. Reviewed weekly by `learnings-engine`.
3. **`core/TOOLS.md` / skill `SKILL.md`** — workflow facts and tool wrappers.
4. **`CLAUDE.md` / `core/rules.md`** — agent-wide constitution.
5. **Hooks (`.claude/settings.json`)** — non-negotiable, machine-enforced.

A repeated mistake at level 1 should be promoted up the pyramid by the next code-review until enforced at the right level.

